Hello all,

The teams will have to fill the entire recipe with ingredients and their
respective quantities in the registration form which will be sent on *28th
Sep, Wednesday at 10 pm*.

On Tue, Sep 27, 2016 at 11:36 AM, Secretary(Hostel Affairs) <
sec_hosaf@smail.iitm.ac.in> wrote:

> Hello all,
>
> The Cooking Club is back with it's Flagship Event for this semester to
> test your culinary prowess and epicurean acumen!
>
> *Game of Chow* is a cooking competition where you've to prove your mettle
> in the kitchen using a few sets of select ingredients.
>
> *What? *Cooking Competition
> *Where? *Himalaya Ground Floor Mess
> *When? *2.30 pm, 2nd October, Sunday
>
>
> *Prizes worth 5k to be won.*
>
>
>
> *Rules and Procedure :*
> 1. This is a team event. Each team should consist of *2 students.*
> 2. Participants will have to choose one set of mandatory ingredients for
> their dish(from any cuisine) from the following list :
>
>    - *Chicken, Sweet Corn, Cashew*
>    - *Fish, Coconut, Mango*
>    - *Mushroom, Capsicum, Basil*
>    - *Paneer, Spring Onions, Green Peas*
>
> *3. *After choosing either 1 set out of the 4 given ingredient sets, the
> participants will *have to make a dish which will comprise the chosen
> ingredients compulsorily*, and any other ingredients as per the recipe.
> It is not mandatory to use all the ingredients in the set chosen for one
> part of the dish only - it can be used as a side too. The more creative,
> the better*!*
>
> *4. *All the ingredients in the recipes chosen by participants will be
> provided by the Cooking Club, given their availability is feasible.
>
> *5. *Teams will be selected based on a first come first serve basis,
> given their recipe is feasible.* Forms for the registration will be sent
> out on **28th Sep, Wednesday at 10 pm*, and participants will be required
> to also include their recipes(serves 2) in these forms.
>
> *6. *At the venue of the event, teams will be provided with *a secret
> ingredient. *It is not compulsory to use this ingredient, but good usage
> of this ingredient would earn extra points for the particular team.
>
> *7. *Teams are allowed to use equipment and ingredients provided by the
> club only.
>
>
> *8. Time Limit : 2 hours*Teams will be required to come at *2.30 pm*, and
> collect their ingredients. They may set up their tables to begin at *3
> pm. *Each team will have to finish assembling their dish by *5 pm*, after
> which the judges will taste their dishes for evaluation.
>
>
>
> *Existing Equipment :*
> All the recipes submitted should be feasible in terms of the ingredients
> required, as well as be prepareable by the existing equipment with the
> Cooking Club. PFA the list of equipment of the club and plan your recipe
> accordingly.
>
> *Look out for Registrations both on our facebook page
> <https://www.facebook.com/cookingIITM/?fref=ts> and smail tomorrow. *
>
> Please Contact Urmika (9677764609) or Ashwanth (8056105066) for further
> queries.
>
> PFA the poster for the Event.
>
> Cheers!
